Background

properties.name: ySalamanderTp
properties.description: Top of Salamander Fork. There is a 35 foot drop here that can be bypassed on the LDC side down a steep slope / chute. (Data by bluugnome.com)

properties.name: R1
properties.description: Rap 1 - Salamander Fork. Anchored from a pinch point on the RDC side and drops about 170 feet down two stages with a possible waist deep pool mid rappel. (Data by bluugnome.com)

properties.name: R2
properties.description: Rap 2 - Salamander Fork. Anchored from a log prtruding from the canyon floor and drops about 90 feet down a slightly sloped slot. Be prepared for a little creative anchor building if the log washes out. (Data by bluugnome.com)

properties.name: R3
properties.description: Rap 3 - Salamander Fork. Anchored from a tree about 15 feet overhead up out of the wash and drops about 15 feet over boulder some boulders. This is also where the canyon begins to slot up again. (Data by bluugnome.com)

properties.name: R4
properties.description: Rap 4 - Salamander Fork. Anchored from a knot chalk about 15 feet back about head high and drops about 10 feet with an awkward overhang. Lots of other anchor options if you prefer another. (Data by bluugnome.com)

properties.name: wSalamander-07
properties.description: Corridor about 100 feet long (wSalamander-07) that is between a side ravine joining in from LDC then a side ravine joining in from RDC. (Data by bluugnome.com)

properties.name: wSalamander-08
properties.description: Cross joint crossing the canyon with narrow slots running up out of the canyon on both sides. This is a little over 100 feet down canyon of a 15 foot downclimb down a fluted wall. (Data by bluugnome.com)

properties.name: R5
properties.description: Rap 5 anchored from log protruding from ground and drops about 15 feet and starts over an overhanging section. (Data by bluugnome.com)

properties.name: R7
properties.description: Rap 7 anchored from a cairn anchor about 10 feet back and drops about 95 feet over 2 stages. The first stage drops down into a large pothole that was sand filled on my first visit but could become a keeper if scoured out by flooding. The top of the second stage of rap 7 (exiting the pothole) has another old star drive bolted anchor. The bolted anchor is old and may not be trustworthy. (Data by bluugnome.com)

properties.name: R8
properties.description: Rap 8 is close to the bottom of rap 7 and is anchored from big logs and drops about 25 feet. At the bottom of rap 8 you are at the end of the Salamander Fork. (Data by bluugnome.com)

properties.name: R6
properties.description: Rap 6 is about 60 feet down canyon of rap 5 and is anchored from a log laying across the wash and drops about 15 feet to a sand filled pothole that could turn to a semi keeper if scoured out. If the log were to wash away there are multiple anchor options using nearby debris or knot chalk or choke stone anchors a few feet back on the LDC side. (Data by bluugnome.com)
